      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "\"Tough on crime\" legislation may show immediate drops in crime rates, but these typically lead to overcrowded prisons and strained resources, ultimately failing to address the root causes of crime. Moreover, such measures disproportionately impact marginalized communities, resulting in higher incarceration rates and long-term socioeconomic harm. True safety and order come from investing in education, mental health resources, and social programs rather than punitive measures.",
